$ Oracle: V$OSSTAT
@ v$osstat

code {
select *
from
   v$osstat
order by case
    when stat_name in ('NUM_CPUS', 'NUM_CPU_CORES', 'NUM_CPU_SOCKETS') then 0
    when stat_name like 'AVG%TIME' then 1
    when stat_name like '%TIME'    then 2
    when stat_name like '%MEMORY%' then 3
    when stat_name like '%BYTES%'  then 4
    else 99 end;
code }

sa:

  The init parameter → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters/cpu/count

  The `→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/sqlpath/cpu` script.

  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views[Oracle Dynamic Performance Views]
